Showing sample image¶

In [11]:
steering = steering_data_angles[1010]
    
left = cv2.imread('./data/'+left_images[1010][1:],1)
left = cv2.cvtColor(left, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
plt.title(steering)
plt.imshow(left)
plt.show()
    
center = cv2.imread('./data/' + center_images[1010],1)
center = cv2.cvtColor(center, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
plt.title(steering)
plt.imshow(center)
plt.show()
    
right = cv2.imread('./data/' + right_images[1010][1:],1)
right = cv2.cvtColor(right, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
plt.title(steering)
plt.imshow(right)
plt.show()

Data Augmentation¶

1- Flipping¶

In [12]:
flipped = []

flipped.append(cv2.flip(left,1))
flipped.append(cv2.flip(center,1))
flipped.append(cv2.flip(right,1))


flipped_steering = - steering

fig = plt.figure(dpi=200)

for image in flipped:

    plt.title(flipped_steering)
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.show()

2- Brightness augmentation¶

In [14]:
fig = plt.figure(dpi=200)

for count in range(3):
    
    image = center
    
    image = cv2.cvtColor(center,cv2.COLOR_RGB2HSV)
    random_bright = .25+np.random.uniform()
    image[:,:,2] = image[:,:,2]*random_bright
    image = cv2.cvtColor(image,cv2.COLOR_HSV2RGB)

    plt.title(steering)
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.show()

3- Horizontal and vertical shifts¶

In [15]:
fig = plt.figure(dpi=200)

for count in range(3):
    
    image = center
    shift_x = 65*np.random.uniform()-65/2
    shift_y = 20*np.random.uniform()-20/2
    shift = np.float32([[1,0,shift_x],[0,1,shift_y]])
                
    rows = image.shape[0]
    cols = image.shape[1]
                
    image = cv2.warpAffine(image,shift,(cols,rows))

    shifted_steering = steering + shift_x/65*.4

    plt.title(shifted_steering)
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.show()

4- Using left and right camera images¶

with adding a small angle to the left camera and subtract a small angle of from the right camera¶

In [16]:
shifted_steering = steering + 0.3

plt.title(shifted_steering)
plt.imshow(left)
plt.show()


shifted_steering = steering - 0.3
plt.title(shifted_steering)
plt.imshow(right)
plt.show()
